What is IIT JEE?

IIT-JEE is a national level joint entrance exam to get admission into bachelor courses in engineering in IITs. JEE is considered one of India's highly competitive engineering exams that require strong analysing and problem-solving skills. At present, there are 23 IITs in India offering a variety of courses ranging from B.Tech to doctoral programs. The Joint Entrance Exam (JEE) is conducted in two phases: JEE Main and JEE Advanced.

JEE Main

JEE Main is the first phase of the entrance test, and only candidates who clear this exam are eligible to appear for JEE Advanced. JEE Main is a computer-based exam and comprises two papers. Paper 1 is conducted to admit candidates to undergraduate engineering programmes in institutes and universities recognised by the State Government. It also serves as an eligibility test for JEE Advanced. Paper 2A and Paper 2B are conducted to admit candidates to B. Arch and B.Planning courses in India.

JEE Main is conducted in the following modes:
  • Paper 1 (BE/B. Tech): Computer Based Test (Online) mode
  • Paper 2A (B. Arch): Mathematics & Aptitude Test in online mode and Drawing Test in offline mode
  • Paper 2B (B. Planning): Mathematics, Aptitude Test and Planning Based Questions in online mode

JEE Advanced

JEE Advanced is the second and final phase of the entrance exam. Candidates who clear JEE Main and score high ranks in the merit list can appear for JEE Advanced. It is a computer-based exam conducted by seven different zonal IITs on a rotational basis. The exam consists of two papers: Paper 1 and Paper 2, carried out in two stages, held on the same day. Learners must appear for both papers to clear IIT-JEE Advanced.

JEE Advanced is conducted in the following modes:
  • Paper 1: It is a Computer Based Test (Online mode). It has multiple-choice questions with a single answer, questions with multiple answers and numerical value answer type questions.
  • Paper 2: It is a Computer Based Test (Online mode). It has multiple correct option type questions, numerical value answer type questions, and matching list type questions.

All sections have an equal number of questions from Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry.

IIT JEE 2022 Eligibility Criteria

The eligibility criteria for IIT-JEE Main and Advanced are quite different. A detailed list of the eligibility criteria for both courses has been mentioned below.

Eligibility Criteria for JEE Main

To appear for JEE Main exam, Learners need to meet the criteria mentioned in the table below:

JEE Main Eligibility Criteria
Required Criteria Details
JEE Main age limit
  • No age limit
Qualifying examination
  • Cleared 10+2 or an equivalent exam from a recognised board/university. Candidates appearing for the 10+2 exam in 2022 can also apply.
10+2 percentage for JEE Main
  • Candidates need to get pass marks in 10+2 to appear for the exam.
Number of attempts
  • Candidates can appear for the JEE Main exam for three consecutive years.
Compulsory subjects
  • Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry/Biology/Biotechnology/Technical Vocational Subject.

Eligibility Criteria for JEE Advanced

Candidates need to fulfil the eligibility criteria mentioned in the table below to appear for JEE Advanced exam:

Required Criteria Details
JEE Advanced age limit
  • Born on or after 1st October 1997. Relaxation of 5 years for reserved category.
Qualifying examination
  • Cleared 10+2 or an equivalent exam from a recognised board/university in 2021. Candidates appearing for the 10+2 exam in 2022 can also apply.
JEE Main
  • Cleared JEE Main and holds rank within the top 2,50,000 candidates (including SC/ST). Candidates also need to meet the cut-off set by IITs
Number of attempts
  • Two attempts in consecutive years.
IIT admissions
  • Candidates should have never taken admission into any IIT. Candidates who joined an IIT and subsequently cancelled their candidature are ineligible to get admission.

IIT JEE 2022 syllabus

National Testing Agency (NTA) is the exam conducting board for JEE Main. It has released the JEE Main syllabus for all the subjects on the official website. The aspiring candidates who will appear for JEE Main 2022 can refer to the detailed syllabus for preparation. Unacademy provides the complete and updated IIT-JEE syllabus to help Learners prepare for the exam. Learners can download the entire IIT-JEE syllabus to start the preparation.

The JEE Main syllabus consists of three main subjects - Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics. All the topics and concepts of Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics from Class 11th and 12th are part of the JEE syllabus. Along with the NCERT syllabus books, candidates can also prepare from reference books recommended in IIT JEE study material. The complete JEE syllabus for all the subjects is given below:

The syllabus for Physics is divided into two sections: Theory and Experimental Skills. The ratio of the weightage of Section A to Section B is 80:20. Chemistry consists of three sections: Physical Chemistry, Inorganic Chemistry and Organic Chemistry. Mathematics includes problems of Algebra, Matrices, Trigonometry, Probability, Analytical Geometry, Calculus, and Vectors.

IIT JEE 2022 Exam Pattern

JEE Main Exam Pattern

JEE Main consists of three papers - Paper 1, Paper 2A and 2B:

Paper 1
  • Paper 1 consists of 90 questions
  • Section A has 60 questions, and Section B has 30 questions
  • Learners need to answer 75 questions - 20 questions in section A and 5 questions in section B for each subject - Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics
  • Section A comprises multiple-choice questions
  • Section B comprises numerical value answer type questions
  • For each correct answer, +4 marks will be awarded, and for each incorrect answer, -1 will be deducted. There Ã­s no negative marking for Section B
Paper 2A
  • Paper 2A consists of 82 questions.
  • Learners can attempt only 77 questions: 25 in Mathematics, 50 in Aptitude and 2 in Drawing
  • In Mathematics, 20 questions will be multiple-choice questions, and 5 questions will be numerical value answer type questions
  • Each correct answer will be marked +4 marks, and -1 will be deducted for each wrong answer
Paper 2B
  • Paper 2B consists of 105 questions.
  • The questions are divided into three parts: Mathematics, Aptitude Test, and Planning based questions
  • Learners can attempt a total of 100 questions
  • The paper will carry a total of 400 marks

JEE Advanced Exam Pattern

JEE Advanced has two papers, and each of them consists of three parts - Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry.

Paper 1

It consists of three sections with 6 MCQs, 8 numerical value answer type questions and 4 paragraph based questions.

Paper 2

It consists of three sections with 6 multiple choice questions, 8 numerical value answer type questions and 4 matching type questions.

IIT JEE 2022: Previous years' question papers with solutions

Learners appearing for JEE Main 2022 can download previous years' question papers with solutions released by the NTA. It will help them prepare for the exam and understand the syllabus weightage. In addition, Learners can also appear for mock tests available on Unacademy. The mock tests by Unacademy help test the knowledge and understand areas that need more preparation.

Study plan for IIT JEE 2022

IIT JEE is one of the toughest exams to pursue a career in the field of engineering. Lots of preparation, hard work and determination are required to crack IIT JEE. The syllabus is vast; therefore, Learners need to have a strategy to prepare for the exam. Preparing a timetable will help divide the syllabus against the number of days each subject takes. Learners can prioritise the syllabus according to their convenience and dedicate more time to tough subjects or topics. Opting for JEE Live Classes from Unacademy is helpful as the Top Educators assist you in preparing well and acing your exam. However, in addition to the Live Classes, self-study is equally important to excel in this exam. Using the right study material, taking mock tests conducted by Unacademy and solving previous years' question papers will help Learners master the topics and perform well in the exam.

Here is a detailed monthly study plan to help JEE aspirants prepare for the exam:

Month 1:

How to select the right Live Class for IIT JEE 2022?

The role of the right guidance is crucial during the preparation of competitive exams like JEE. It is a long journey that starts with small steps, which involves choosing Top Educators for preparation. A lot of Learners are opting for Live Classes on Unacademy to aid their preparation. Unlimited access to structured Live Classes is one of the reasons Learners prefer Unacademy.

Online learning is helpful in many ways, provided you select the right platform that helps boost your preparation. While shortlisting, keep in mind that it is the experience of the Educator that plays a crucial role in helping you understand the concepts and prepare better for the exam.

Here are some essentials factors to consider while selecting the right Live Class and Top Educators for IIT JEE preparation:

Track the success record

Check the success rate of the online ed-tech platform in competitive exams. Take feedback from the existing and past students and ask them about the facilities and study materials that the platform provides for preparation.

Check the profile of the Educators

Look for an online learning platform with experienced Educators who can help Learners understand the syllabus and test pattern. Take feedback from students of previous batches about how well they teach. Top Educators on Unacademy equip Learners with tips and tricks to solve complex problems with speed and accuracy.

Inspect the study material provided by the online learning platform

Every online learning platform provides study material to Learners that consist of textbooks, mock test papers, question banks, solved question papers of previous years, etc. Go through the study material provided.

Mantras to get through IIT JEE 2022

Preparing for JEE can be challenging, especially when the competition is fierce and youÃ­re contending against the countryÃ­s brightest minds. It is usual to come under immense pressure when the exam is just around the corner. To help you out, we have prepared a list of tips to take the pressure off your mind and increase your chances of scoring well in the exam.

Start on time

The syllabus for JEE is vast; therefore, it is important to start preparing on time. If you are clear about opting for Engineering as a career, you must start JEE preparation at the beginning of Class 9.

Understand the exam pattern

The next step is to find out the JEE pattern and plan your preparation accordingly to achieve the desired result. You can also appear for the mock tests available on Unacademy to understand the exam pattern and evaluate the areas that need improvement.

Know the syllabus

The complete overview of the syllabus will help you gain information about important chapters, topics and other meaningful details. It will help you develop a preparation strategy to master the subjects and crack JEE. You can download the complete IIT-JEE syllabus from Unacademy.

Use the right study material

Generally, NCERT books are recommended for JEE preparation, but there are other books, question banks and mock test papers available online that you can refer to for deep understanding.

Set targets

Challenge yourself every day. Setting targets will help you achieve results and keep you motivated. Make sure you start with small and achievable targets. It will boost your confidence and encourage you to achieve a bigger target.

Keep practicing

During the JEE preparation, attempt mock tests to get familiar with the exam pattern and increase your chances of success. Solve previous years' question papers to get familiar with the types of questions asked in JEE.

What is IIT JEE?

IIT-JEE is a national level joint entrance exam to get admission into bachelor courses in engineering in IITs. JEE is considered one of India's highly competitive engineering exams that require strong analysing and problem-solving skills. At present, there are 23 IITs in India offering a variety of courses ranging from B.Tech to doctoral programs. The Joint Entrance Exam (JEE) is conducted in two phases: JEE Main and JEE Advanced.

JEE Main

JEE Main is the first phase of the entrance test, and only candidates who clear this exam are eligible to appear for JEE Advanced. JEE Main is a computer-based exam and comprises two papers. Paper 1 is conducted to admit candidates to undergraduate engineering programmes in institutes and universities recognised by the State Government. It also serves as an eligibility test for JEE Advanced. Paper 2A and Paper 2B are conducted to admit candidates to B. Arch and B.Planning courses in India.

JEE Main is conducted in the following modes:
  • Paper 1 (BE/B. Tech): Computer Based Test (Online) mode
  • Paper 2A (B. Arch): Mathematics & Aptitude Test in online mode and Drawing Test in offline mode
  • Paper 2B (B. Planning): Mathematics, Aptitude Test and Planning Based Questions in online mode

JEE Advanced

JEE Advanced is the second and final phase of the entrance exam. Candidates who clear JEE Main and score high ranks in the merit list can appear for JEE Advanced. It is a computer-based exam conducted by seven different zonal IITs on a rotational basis. The exam consists of two papers: Paper 1 and Paper 2, carried out in two stages, held on the same day. Learners must appear for both papers to clear IIT-JEE Advanced.

JEE Advanced is conducted in the following modes:
  • Paper 1: It is a Computer Based Test (Online mode). It has multiple-choice questions with a single answer, questions with multiple answers and numerical value answer type questions.
  • Paper 2: It is a Computer Based Test (Online mode). It has multiple correct option type questions, numerical value answer type questions, and matching list type questions.

All sections have an equal number of questions from Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry.

IIT JEE 2022 Eligibility Criteria

The eligibility criteria for IIT-JEE Main and Advanced are quite different. A detailed list of the eligibility criteria for both courses has been mentioned below.

Eligibility Criteria for JEE Main

To appear for JEE Main exam, Learners need to meet the criteria mentioned in the table below:

JEE Main Eligibility Criteria
Required Criteria Details
JEE Main age limit
  • No age limit
Qualifying examination
  • Cleared 10+2 or an equivalent exam from a recognised board/university. Candidates appearing for the 10+2 exam in 2022 can also apply.
10+2 percentage for JEE Main
  • Candidates need to get pass marks in 10+2 to appear for the exam.
Number of attempts
  • Candidates can appear for the JEE Main exam for three consecutive years.
Compulsory subjects
  • Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry/Biology/Biotechnology/Technical Vocational Subject.

Eligibility Criteria for JEE Advanced

Candidates need to fulfil the eligibility criteria mentioned in the table below to appear for JEE Advanced exam:

Required Criteria Details
JEE Advanced age limit
  • Born on or after 1st October 1997. Relaxation of 5 years for reserved category.
Qualifying examination
  • Cleared 10+2 or an equivalent exam from a recognised board/university in 2021. Candidates appearing for the 10+2 exam in 2022 can also apply.
JEE Main
  • Cleared JEE Main and holds rank within the top 2,50,000 candidates (including SC/ST). Candidates also need to meet the cut-off set by IITs
Number of attempts
  • Two attempts in consecutive years.
IIT admissions
  • Candidates should have never taken admission into any IIT. Candidates who joined an IIT and subsequently cancelled their candidature are ineligible to get admission.

IIT JEE 2022 syllabus

National Testing Agency (NTA) is the exam conducting board for JEE Main. It has released the JEE Main syllabus for all the subjects on the official website. The aspiring candidates who will appear for JEE Main 2022 can refer to the detailed syllabus for preparation. Unacademy provides the complete and updated IIT-JEE syllabus to help Learners prepare for the exam. Learners can download the entire IIT-JEE syllabus to start the preparation.

The JEE Main syllabus consists of three main subjects - Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics. All the topics and concepts of Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics from Class 11th and 12th are part of the JEE syllabus. Along with the NCERT syllabus books, candidates can also prepare from reference books recommended in IIT JEE study material. The complete JEE syllabus for all the subjects is given below:

The syllabus for Physics is divided into two sections: Theory and Experimental Skills. The ratio of the weightage of Section A to Section B is 80:20. Chemistry consists of three sections: Physical Chemistry, Inorganic Chemistry and Organic Chemistry. Mathematics includes problems of Algebra, Matrices, Trigonometry, Probability, Analytical Geometry, Calculus, and Vectors.

IIT JEE 2022 Exam Pattern

JEE Main Exam Pattern

JEE Main consists of three papers - Paper 1, Paper 2A and 2B:

Paper 1
  • Paper 1 consists of 90 questions
  • Section A has 60 questions, and Section B has 30 questions
  • Learners need to answer 75 questions - 20 questions in section A and 5 questions in section B for each subject - Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics
  • Section A comprises multiple-choice questions
  • Section B comprises numerical value answer type questions
  • For each correct answer, +4 marks will be awarded, and for each incorrect answer, -1 will be deducted. There Ã­s no negative marking for Section B
Paper 2A
  • Paper 2A consists of 82 questions.
  • Learners can attempt only 77 questions: 25 in Mathematics, 50 in Aptitude and 2 in Drawing
  • In Mathematics, 20 questions will be multiple-choice questions, and 5 questions will be numerical value answer type questions
  • Each correct answer will be marked +4 marks, and -1 will be deducted for each wrong answer
Paper 2B
  • Paper 2B consists of 105 questions.
  • The questions are divided into three parts: Mathematics, Aptitude Test, and Planning based questions
  • Learners can attempt a total of 100 questions
  • The paper will carry a total of 400 marks

JEE Advanced Exam Pattern

JEE Advanced has two papers, and each of them consists of three parts - Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry.

Paper 1

It consists of three sections with 6 MCQs, 8 numerical value answer type questions and 4 paragraph based questions.

Paper 2

It consists of three sections with 6 multiple choice questions, 8 numerical value answer type questions and 4 matching type questions.

IIT JEE 2022: Previous years' question papers with solutions

Learners appearing for JEE Main 2022 can download previous years' question papers with solutions released by the NTA. It will help them prepare for the exam and understand the syllabus weightage. In addition, Learners can also appear for mock tests available on Unacademy. The mock tests by Unacademy help test the knowledge and understand areas that need more preparation.

Study plan for IIT JEE 2022

IIT JEE is one of the toughest exams to pursue a career in the field of engineering. Lots of preparation, hard work and determination are required to crack IIT JEE. The syllabus is vast; therefore, Learners need to have a strategy to prepare for the exam. Preparing a timetable will help divide the syllabus against the number of days each subject takes. Learners can prioritise the syllabus according to their convenience and dedicate more time to tough subjects or topics. Opting for JEE Live Classes from Unacademy is helpful as the Top Educators assist you in preparing well and acing your exam. However, in addition to the Live Classes, self-study is equally important to excel in this exam. Using the right study material, taking mock tests conducted by Unacademy and solving previous years' question papers will help Learners master the topics and perform well in the exam.

Here is a detailed monthly study plan to help JEE aspirants prepare for the exam:

Month 1:

Mantras to get through IIT JEE 2022

Preparing for JEE can be challenging, especially when the competition is fierce and youÃ­re contending against the countryÃ­s brightest minds. It is usual to come under immense pressure when the exam is just around the corner. To help you out, we have prepared a list of tips to take the pressure off your mind and increase your chances of scoring well in the exam.

Start on time

The syllabus for JEE is vast; therefore, it is important to start preparing on time. If you are clear about opting for Engineering as a career, you must start JEE preparation at the beginning of Class 9.

Understand the exam pattern

The next step is to find out the JEE pattern and plan your preparation accordingly to achieve the desired result. You can also appear for the mock tests available on Unacademy to understand the exam pattern and evaluate the areas that need improvement.

Know the syllabus

The complete overview of the syllabus will help you gain information about important chapters, topics and other meaningful details. It will help you develop a preparation strategy to master the subjects and crack JEE. You can download the complete IIT-JEE syllabus from Unacademy.

Use the right study material

Generally, NCERT books are recommended for JEE preparation, but there are other books, question banks and mock test papers available online that you can refer to for deep understanding.

Set targets

Challenge yourself every day. Setting targets will help you achieve results and keep you motivated. Make sure you start with small and achievable targets. It will boost your confidence and encourage you to achieve a bigger target.

Keep practicing

During the JEE preparation, attempt mock tests to get familiar with the exam pattern and increase your chances of success. Solve previous years' question papers to get familiar with the types of questions asked in JEE.
